  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    /* Navbar Styling */
    .navbar {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between; /* Push content to edges */
      align-items: center; /* Vertically center items */
      background-color: #4CAF50;
      padding: 10px;
    }

    /* Styling for the logo on the left */
    .navbar .logo {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      color: white;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    /* Navbar button form styling */
    .navbar form {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-right: 15px;
    }

    /* Button styling */
    .navbar button {
      color: white;
      background-color: #4CAF50;
      border: none;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    /* Hover effect for buttons */
    .navbar button:hover {
      background-color: #45a049;
    }

    .container {
      padding: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Navigation Bar -->
  <div class="navbar">
    <!-- Logo on the left side -->
    <div class="logo">
      Turtle Shelter
    </div>

    <!-- Navbar Buttons (aligned to the right) -->
    <div class="nav-buttons">
      <!-- Home Button Form -->
      <form action="/" method="GET">
        <button type="submit">Home</button>
      </form>

      <!-- Event Management Button Form -->
      <form action="/eventManagement" method="GET">
        <button type="submit">Event Management</button>
      </form>

      <!-- Volunteer Request Button Form -->
      <form action="/volunteerForm" method="GET">
        <button type="submit">Volunteer Form</button>
      </form>

      <!-- Event Request Button Form -->
      <form action="/EventRequestForm" method="GET">
        <button type="submit">Event Request</button>
      </form>

      <!-- Volunteer Management Button Form -->
      <form action="/volunteerManagement" method="GET">
        <button type="submit">Volunteer Management</button>
      </form>

      <!-- Admin Login Button Form -->
      <form action="/adminLogin" method="GET">
        <button type="submit">Admin Login</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Welcome to the Turtle Shelter Project</h1>
    <h1>Who we are</h1>
    <p>TSP is your organization dedicated to bringing homeless people the protection they need through high-tech winter vests.</p>
    <p>One winter when Jen was homeless, 7 of her friends froze to death. After surmounting her own journey from the frigid cold, she was determined to figure out a solution to help others with this burden. She created an inexpensive high-tech solution with the help of a survival expert that helps SAVE lives and more importantly alleviate suffering.</p>
    <p>There is no need for those in a state of emergency to have to pay so much on top of the burden of recovering.</p>
    <br><br>
    <h1>What we do</h1>
    <p>We answer the call to spread warmth in the lives of the homeless who are vulnerable to harsh winters by creating portable "shelters" that they can carry with them, just like a turtle.</p>
    <p>Although increased homeless services, especially additional shelter availability, are necessary to accommodate the amplified need in the winter, life-threatening hypothermia can set in between 32-50 degrees, which is not cold enough for many winter shelters to open.</p>
    <p>Our technology is about more than just making sure that the wearer maintains heat from their core. The warmth that our vests provide restores confidence, energy, and hope.</p>
    <h1>How you can help</h1>
    <b><p>"Every life has value, every person can serve", and you can take the next step to donate, make vests, and organize an event too!</p></b>
    <P>Be a part of a powerful campaign that changes lives of those in need.</P>
  </div>

</body>
</html>


  
